72":"1372","about 1330":"about 1330","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Denmark":"Denmark","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Donald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Gaelic Domhnall . The final <i>-d</i> of the Anglicized form derives partly from misinterpretation by English speakers of the Gaelic pronunciation, and partly from association with Germanic-origin names such as   Ronald .  This name is strongly associated with clan Macdonald, the clan of the medieval Lords of the Isles, but is now also widely used by families with no Scottish connections."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Bild","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered short form of   William  , not used before the 19th century. The reason for the change in the initial consonant is not clear, but it conforms to the pattern regularly found when English words beginning with <i>w-</i> are borrowed into Gaelic. The nickname ‘King Billy’ for  William  of Orange is an early example from Ireland, which may have influenced English usage. It is bestowed occasionally as a name in its own right."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Donald Bild de Frostenden Constable was born about 1310, in Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Esge Anderson Frost Bild, was 11308 and his mother, Hustru, was 12. He married Arvegods about 1330, in Denmark. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1310–":"umbes 1310–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1312–Female":"1312–Surnud","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1298–1346":"1298–1346","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","Abt 1310":"umbes 1310","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1298":"1298","Abt 1337":"umbes 1337","1372":"1372","about 1330":"umbes 1330","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Denmark":"Taani"},"fi":{"Abt 1310–":"noin 1310–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1312–Female":"1312–Kuollut","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1298–1346":"1298–1346","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","Abt 1310":"noin 1310","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1298":"1298","Abt 1337":"noin 1337","1372":"1372","about 1330":"noin 1330","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Denmark":"Tanska"},"fr":{"Abt 1310–":"environ 1310–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1312–Female":"1312–Décédée","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1298–1346":"1298–1346","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1312":"1312","Abt 1310":"environ 1310","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1298":"1298","Abt 1337":"environ 1337","1372":"1372","about 1330":"environ 1330","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Denmark":"Danemark","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Donald Bild de Frostenden Constable est né environ 1310, à Frostenden, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Sir Esge Anderson Frost Bild, avait 11308 ans et sa mère, Hustru, avait 12 ans. Il a épousé Arvegods environ 1330, à Danemark. Ils on